<p class="article-lead">Before importing perfume from China, close the gaps between the sales contract, destination compliance and freight booking.</p><ul><li>Verify the supplier identity, manufacturing scope and approved specification.</li><li>Assign the importer or Responsible Person and complete formula and label review.</li><li>Approve fragrance, components, artwork and the finished pre-production sample.</li><li>Confirm Incoterm, dangerous-goods route, insurance and destination charges.</li><li>Prepare consistent invoice, packing list, marks and product information.</li><li>Arrange inspection and define how defects are reported.</li></ul><p>Use a customs broker and qualified regulatory adviser for the importing country. Factory documents support their work but do not transfer the buyer's market-entry responsibility.</p>
